DIV2.P:
Their publike Almes is a sacrifice or offering of some beast
for a sacrifice vnto Mahomet once euery yéere: which being kil∣led,
it is cut into small péeces, and giuen all to the poore.

At our returne to Ierusalem, they brought vs to mount Oli∣uet,
from whence our Sauiour Christ ascended into Heauen,
being from Ierusalem a Sabboth daies iourney, not two miles.
